des:
Realme Link helps you control home appliance. You can simply ask Alexa to turn on or turn off your smart device.

There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your smart device - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show.

After connecting Alexa to realme Link in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "realme Link" app in android app market;
(2). Register one account in our "realme Link" app;
(3). You need to have some realme smart devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our "realme Link" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "realme Link" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "realme Link" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "realme Link", and you'll be navigated to realme Link login page;
(9). Input your realme Link account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished.

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa,turn on the bedroom light.”
“Alexa,turn off the bedroom light.”
“Alexa,set the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa,brighten the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa,dim the bedroom light to 50%.”
"Alexa, set bedroom light to green."
"Alexa, set bedroom light to cool white."
